270
00:12:38,580 --> 00:12:40,540
and over the cattle and over all the earth

271
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:43,580
and over every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth.

272
00:12:43,580 --> 00:12:47,540
So God created man in his own image

273
00:12:47,540 --> 00:12:50,180
and the image of God created he him male and female

274
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:53,100
created he them and God blessed them.

275
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:55,380
And God said unto them, be fruitful and multiply

276
00:12:55,380 --> 00:12:57,460
and replenish the earth and subdue it

277
00:12:57,460 --> 00:12:59,580
and have dominion over the fish of the sea

278
00:12:59,580 --> 00:13:02,820
and over the fowl of the air and over every living thing

279
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:05,260
that moveth upon the earth.

280
00:13:05,260 --> 00:13:08,660
God said, behold, I have given you every herb bearing seed

281
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:10,460
which is upon the face of all the earth

282
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:12,740
and every tree and the which is the fruit

283
00:13:12,740 --> 00:13:17,740
of a tree yielding seed to you it shall be for meat.

284
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:20,700
To every beast of the earth and every fowl of the air

285
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:23,020
and to everything that creepeth upon the earth

286
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:26,460
wherein there is life I have given every green herb

287
00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:28,580
for meat and it was so.

288
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:33,580
Notice verse 31, and God saw everything that he had made

289
00:13:34,540 --> 00:13:37,740
and behold, it was very good.

290
00:13:37,740 --> 00:13:42,060
And the evening and the morning were the sixth day.

291
00:13:42,060 --> 00:13:43,860
Six days of creation.

292
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:47,020
31 verses in our English Bibles.

293
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:50,300
32 references to the name Elohim.

294
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:52,940
Now let me say this before we get into some application.

295
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:57,700
This evening Elohim is the plural form of El.

296
00:13:58,980 --> 00:14:02,580
Notice as we look through and we'll study in weeks to come

297
00:14:02,580 --> 00:14:06,300
that El is often used and we'll note it in the future

298
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:09,980
compound usage with other names of God.

299
00:14:09,980 --> 00:14:13,340
El Elyon, El Shaddai.

300
00:14:13,340 --> 00:14:15,460
And we see there's a number of them

301
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:16,540
and we'll look at those.

302
00:14:16,540 --> 00:14:19,420
And so when you begin to think about the singular El

303
00:14:19,420 --> 00:14:23,300
versus the plural Elohim and here throughout

304
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:26,060
the Genesis 1 record dealing with that

305
00:14:26,060 --> 00:14:30,900
inherent in the plurality of the term is the Trinity.

306
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:33,260
And I believe that you see that right from the opening

307
00:14:33,260 --> 00:14:37,020
pages of scripture and you consider the progressive aspect

308
00:14:37,020 --> 00:14:40,380
of progressive revelation and how God introduces

309
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:42,580
this truth to us even in Genesis 1.

310
00:14:42,580 --> 00:14:47,580
We read in verse 26, let us make man in our image.

311
00:14:47,740 --> 00:14:48,620
Plural.

312
00:14:48,620 --> 00:14:51,260
And we find that throughout the scriptures

313
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:54,580
with that progressive revelation we see with great clarity

314
00:14:54,580 --> 00:14:58,020
the truth and teaching of the Trinity.

315
00:14:58,020 --> 00:15:01,100
It's of interest of course as you consider

316
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,380
throughout the pages of scripture

317
00:15:03,380 --> 00:15:06,980
that the name Elohim is specifically connected

318
00:15:06,980 --> 00:15:09,700
to the subject of creation as we see here

319
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:11,700
in Genesis chapter number one.

320
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:14,180
But as you read in Psalm chapter 33

321
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:15,860
and we won't take the time this evening

322
00:15:15,860 --> 00:15:17,260
to go there and read it.

323
00:15:17,260 --> 00:15:22,260
But as you read Psalm 33 speaking much about creation

324
00:15:22,260 --> 00:15:27,260
it's the name Jehovah that is used to describe creation.

325
00:15:27,420 --> 00:15:28,820
Is there a contradiction?

326
00:15:28,820 --> 00:15:29,980
Of course not.

327
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:32,740
There are various names of the same God

328
00:15:32,740 --> 00:15:36,460
that reveal to us aspects of his nature

329
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:38,140
and of his character.

330
00:15:38,140 --> 00:15:41,340
Furthermore as you get into the New Testament

331
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:46,140
you find that it's through Jesus that he is the creator.

332
00:15:46,140 --> 00:15:49,300
John chapter number one in verse number three.

333
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:52,540
Colossians chapter number one verses 16 and 17.

334
00:15:52,540 --> 00:15:57,540
Very plain that Jesus Christ is the one

335
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:00,060
that is active in creation.

336
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:02,900
He is God.

337
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:05,660
It's a beautiful truth that God gives us

338
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:07,420
