345
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:30,460
How does knowing the name Elohim impact the people of God?

346
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:33,580
Can I say it this way tonight?

347
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:38,100
Oftentimes we use the name God and we can use it generically.

348
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:43,420
In fact there are people of other world religions

349
00:16:43,420 --> 00:16:48,220
that are not offended by the name God.

350
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:51,500
Because in their mind it can be whatever God

351
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,780
they want it to be.

352
00:16:53,780 --> 00:16:56,900
And we find that often we speak about the importance

353
00:16:56,900 --> 00:17:01,140
of speaking the name Jesus because Jesus makes

354
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:03,820
a distinction that we're talking about

355
00:17:03,820 --> 00:17:06,780
the Lord Jesus Christ, the Messiah.

356
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:09,820
But we understand this evening that as we read Genesis

357
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:12,060
and as we read much of the Old Testament

358
00:17:12,060 --> 00:17:15,580
that we don't see the Hebrew names of God, why?

359
00:17:15,580 --> 00:17:17,340
Because we don't speak Hebrew.

360
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:23,180
So we see the English translation of the word, of the name.

361
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:27,540
And so we do not read Elohim and think strong one,

362
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:29,780
