363
00:17:29,780 --> 00:17:33,300
But we understand that as we dig in and we understand

364
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:37,220
these names of God and we see the various aspects

365
00:17:37,220 --> 00:17:41,500
and various aspects of the attributes and character of God

366
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:43,460
that are being communicated to us,

367
00:17:43,460 --> 00:17:46,820
that it impacts our lives.

368
00:17:46,820 --> 00:17:50,580
Because our God is the creator.

369
00:17:50,580 --> 00:17:54,740
Our God is the one that said let there be light

370
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:55,860
and there was light.

371
00:17:55,860 --> 00:17:58,300
He's the one that made the stars also.

372
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:02,180
He's the one that made us in his image.

373
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:05,260
He's the one that through the week of creation

374
00:18:05,260 --> 00:18:08,820
revealed his power and his wisdom.

375
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:12,460
And he's our God and we can go to him.

376
00:18:13,700 --> 00:18:16,540
Knowing that he hears and answers, knowing that

377
00:18:16,540 --> 00:18:19,820
if he could create everything out of nothing,

378
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:24,300
then what problem do we have, what difficulty do we have

379
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:25,940
that's too difficult for him?

380
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:29,860
Absolutely nothing, amen?

381
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:31,580
Because he can do all things.

382
00:18:31,940 --> 00:18:33,940
I want you to consider a few examples.

383
00:18:33,940 --> 00:18:35,500
I don't know that we'll have time to look at all of them,

384
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:37,820
but look over the book of Isaiah, if you will,

